com.google.android.exoplayer2.extractor.ogg

Interface OggSeeker

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultOggSeeker, FlacReader.FlacOggSeeker, StreamReader.UnseekableOggSeeker

    interface OggSeeker
    Used to seek in an Ogg stream. OggSeeker implementation may do direct seeking or progressive seeking. OggSeeker works together with a SeekMap instance to capture the queried position and start the seeking with an initial estimated position.

      • createSeekMap

        SeekMap createSeekMap()
        Returns a SeekMap that returns an initial estimated position for progressive seeking or the final position for direct seeking. Returns null if read(com.google.android.exoplayer2.extractor.ExtractorInput) has yet to return -1.

      • read

        long read(ExtractorInput input)
   throws java.io.IOException,
          java.lang.InterruptedException
        Reads data from the ExtractorInput to build the SeekMap or to continue a progressive seek.

        If more data is required or if the position of the input needs to be modified then a position from which data should be provided is returned. Else a negative value is returned. If a seek has been completed then the value returned is -(currentGranule + 2). Else it is -1.

        Parameters:
        input - The ExtractorInput to read from.
        Returns:
        A non-negative position to seek the ExtractorInput to, or -(currentGranule + 2) if the progressive seek has completed, or -1 otherwise.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If reading from the ExtractorInput fails.
        java.lang.InterruptedException - If the thread is interrupted.
